[1] USA: doctor from Sierra Leone dies in Nebraska hospital
Date: 17 Nov 2014
Source: Washington Post [edited]
http://www.washingtonpost.com/national/surgeon-with-ebola-died-nebraska-hospital-says/2014/11/17/9192171c-6e5e-11e4-a2c2-478179fd0489_story.html?wpisrc=al_national


A surgeon who contracted Ebola while working in his native Sierra Leone has died while being treated in a biocontainment unit at a Nebraska hospital, the facility said Monday [17 Nov 2014].

Nebraska Medical Center said in a news release that [the doctor] died as a result of the disease. "[He] was extremely critical when he arrived here, and unfortunately, despite out best efforts, we weren't able to save him," said Dr. Phil Smith, medical director of the biocontainment unit. [The doctor] arrived Sat [15 Nov 2014] to be treated at the Omaha hospital, where 2 other Ebola patients have been successfully treated.

The 44-year-old [doctor] had been working as a general surgeon at Kissy United Methodist Hospital in the Sierra Leone capital of Freetown. It's not clear whether he was involved in the care of Ebola patients. Kissy is not an Ebola treatment unit, but Salia worked in at least 3 other facilities, United Methodist News said, citing health ministry sources. [The doctor], a Sierra Leone citizen who lives in Maryland, 1st showed Ebola symptoms on 6 Nov 2014 but tested negative for the virus. He eventually tested positive on 10 Nov 2014.

